comments.body: i *think* this file can be empty (but check other contrib/../python/ directories)

Well, this file by @martinwicke isn't either:
https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/contrib/nn/python/__init__.py
Is there any special intent behind this?

Empty __init__.py files can either be completely empty, or they can contain license headers, py3 compatibility imports, and nothing else. I would prefer completely empty, but it doesn't matter much either way.
